Firebird and Trans AM (Enthusiast Color Series)
MBI Publishing Company | 2002 | 076031165X | English | 100 pages | PDF | 15 MB

This full-color history chronicles Pontiac's Firebird and Trans Am from 1967 to today. The Firebird hit the market as a response to the Ford Mustang and Mercury Cougar. Firebirds became an extremely popular car, but then the Trans Am came along offering more horsepower, more performance, a better package, and a "bad" look. For more than 30 years, both models headed Pontiac's performance list; they still attract a lot of attention
